The Ohanaeze Ndigbo Youth Council Worldwide has lauded Abia State governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, and other prominent Igbo leaders for their assistance when President General Okechukwu Isiguzoro was involved in auto crash. According to a statement signed by Deputy President General, Comrade Obinna Achionye and the Secretary-General Mazi Okwu Nnabuike, the OYC recalled that Isiguzoro, was involved in an accident in 2018 while on a national assignment that is of Igbo’s interests. It was the Abia State governor who single-handedly footed the medical bills of Mazi Okechukwu Isiguzoro and others for 20 months in India. This kind gesture will never be forgotten in the annals of Ndigbo. Igbo youths are grateful to Governor Okezie ikpeazu. “We are equally proud of Governor Dave Umahi, Mr Peter Obi,Dame Patience Jonathan, Foreign Affairs Minister, Geoffrey Onyeama, Ogbonnaya onu and Chibuike Amaechi for their support to Isiguzoro and his family, and the prayers of Christian Association of Nigeria Youth wing,Nigieria Ethnic Nationalities Youth Forum led by Yerima Shettima, Amb Sokubo Sokubo National Youth Council of Nigeria President, and most importantly to God Almighty for the resuscitation of Isiguzoro. OYC will announce the date and venue of the Thanksgiving service for Mazi Okechukwu Isiguzoro on his birthday by ending of December 2020.”